      "message": "i don\u0027t think that\u0027s accurate.  what you describe is a complicated CLI which means it\u0027s complicated for users.  whether it be argparse or something else, it won\u0027t be easy to support because it isn\u0027t straight forward.\n\nsupporting args that are comma or whitespace delimited is actually fairly easy in argparse.  it doesn\u0027t mean it\u0027s a good idea though as both of those are valid filename components.  i understand that this is \"standard\" in the google3 world, but that\u0027s because the google3 world constrains itself and doesn\u0027t care about anything beyond its limited world view.",
